-- Italy's UBI Banca Is Said to Be Planning Sale of Seven-Year Covered Bonds
-- Caroline Hyde
-- 2010-06-21T08:12:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/italy-s-ubi-banca-is-said-to-be-planning-sale-of-seven-year-covered-bonds.html

          
          
             Unione di Banche Italiane SCPA plans
to sell seven-year covered bonds in euros, according to three
people with knowledge of the sale.  
 The notes may be priced to yield about 95 basis points more
than the benchmark mid-swap rate, the people said. Barcalys
Capital, Credit Agricole CIB, UniCredit SpA and UBS AG are
managing the sale, the people said.  
          
          


  


        